[Daniel 8:13](../../../bib/kjv/dan008.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">dan 8:13</span></span>

desolation

Seven times in Daniel the "desolation" is spoken of:

\(1\) Of the sanctuary, ([Dan 8:13](../../../bib/kjv/dan008.htm#013).md)
fulfilled by Antiochus Epiphanes, B.C. 175-170.

\(2\) Of the sanctuary, ([Dan 9:17](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#017).md)
the condition in Daniel's time, when the Jews were in exile and the
sanctuary desolate.

\(3\) Generally, of the land, ([Dan
9:18](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#018).md) also referring to Daniel's time.

\(4\) Of the sanctuary, ([Dan 9:26](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#026).md)
fulfilled A.D. 70, in the destruction of city and temple after the
cutting off of Messiah. ([Luk 21:20](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#020).md).

(5, 6, 7) Of the sanctuary, by the Beast, ([Dan
9:27](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#027).md); ([Dan
11:31](../../../bib/kjv/dan011.htm#031).md); ([Dan
12:11](../../../bib/kjv/dan012.htm#011).md).

Compare ([Mat 24:15](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#015).md); ([Mar
13:14](../../../bib/kjv/mar013.htm#014).md); ([Th2
2:3](../../../bib/kjv/th2002.htm#003).md); ([Th2
2:8-12](../../../bib/kjv/th2002.htm#008).md); ([Rev
13:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev013.htm#014).md); ([Rev
13:15](../../../bib/kjv/rev013.htm#015).md).

one saint

Or, holy one, idem. ([Dan 4:13](../../../bib/kjv/dan004.htm#013).md); ([Dan
4:17](../../../bib/kjv/dan004.htm#017).md).

