[Daniel 8:19](../../../bib/kjv/dan008.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">dan 8:19</span></span>

end

Two "ends" are in view here:

\(1\) historically, the end of the third, or Grecian empire of Alexander
out of one of the divisions of which the little horn of verse 9 ([Dan
8:9](../../../bib/kjv/dan008.htm#009)) (Antiochus.md) arose;

\(2\) prophetically, the end of the times of the Gentiles ([Luk
21:24](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#024).md); ([Rev
16:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#014).md) when the "little horn" of ([Dan
7:8](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#008).md); ([Dan
7:24-26](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#024).md) the Beast, will arise --
Daniel's final time of the end.

(See Scofield) - ([Dan 12:4](../../../bib/kjv/dan012.htm#004).md).

